procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Extracted the data set from TomTom MultiNet Post v. 2011.06. Clipped to the coastline with Data & Maps 2012 U.S. States. Dissolved on the ZIP field to make features multi-part. Created the STATE field via the geoprocessing tool Identity with Data & Maps 2012 U.S. States. Attached and formatted the fields from 2010 Census Summary File 1 and Esri Data. Added the SQMI field and calculated its values projected to Albers Equal Area. Recalculated the POP00_SQMI and POP10_SQMI fields with the new SQMI values. Put "-99" values into all number type fields (except SQMI) for records where there were no matches. Converted the data set to SDC. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.

horizpa.horizpar: Horizontal positional accuracy is dependent on geographic area. In most areas, accuracy is between 5 and 25 meters (16 and 82 feet). In some areas, accuracy is off by up to several tens of meters (100 feet or more). In the poorest areas, accuracy is off by up to 100 meters (328 feet).

dataqual.logic: The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using tools in ArcGIS. The SDC data set is then imported into a file geodatabase to verify, validate, and if needed repair the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
